\subsection{Uncertainty as a Reliability Signal}

\begin{figure}[t]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=\columnwidth]{figures/fig_observation}
\caption{Ranking quality declines monotonically as \method{} uncertainty rises.
Mean NDCG@10 across the four diagnostic domains is plotted against the
\method{} uncertainty quantile bin (Q01 lowest to Q05 highest), for \method{}
and for the strongest reranking baseline, LLMEmb, scored on the
\emph{same} events. Both methods drop from the low- to the high-uncertainty
bin, so the signal stratifies same-candidate reliability for the baseline too.
For \method{} the stratification is partly mechanical---events are binned by
\method{}'s own uncertainty and its ranking score is a monotone function of the
same posterior---so we read the figure descriptively; the cross-method decline
on LLMEmb is the motivation. Values match the per-bin rows underlying
Table~\ref{tab:uncertainty_stratification}.}
